		<title>14          REVENUE</title>
		<content> The 60,000 or so Summer tourists that 
 visit Sark bring in most of the       
 Islands' income by staying at island  
 hotels,visiting local shops,cafes and 
 pubs.                                 
 The boat fare paid by all visitors to 
 Sark includes a "landing tax" which is
 currently 45p and this goes into the  
 islands "purse" to help pay for the   
 doctor,teachers,Island workmen and the
 general upkeep of Sark.               
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
